Description:
   Veteran's Cadence is a Crusader passive combat rhythm technique. Through
   extensive campaign experience, the Crusader has internalized an optimal
   attack rhythm that sustains high offensive output over long engagements.
   Each successful attack in the cadence builds momentum, slightly improving
   the speed and power of subsequent attacks.

   The cadence is a flowing pattern of attacks — not a fixed sequence, but
   an adaptive rhythm that the Crusader maintains instinctively. It improves
   attack speed and serves as the foundation for the Crusader's combo system.
   Maintaining the cadence through a long fight gives Crusaders a significant
   endurance advantage over opponents whose combat intensity fades over time.
   The cadence breaks if the Crusader is stunned or forced to halt their
   attack rhythm.
